{"questionId":"22633","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Natasha carries out an experiment on the growth of mould. She believes that the growth can&nbsp;be modelled by an exponential function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>,</p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> is the area covered by mould in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>mm</mtext><mtext>2</mtext></msup></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time in days since the start of the&nbsp;experiment and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> are constants.</p>\n<p>The area covered by mould is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>112</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>mm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math> at the start of the experiment and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>mm</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math> after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> days.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>112</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22633","referenceCode":"21N.1.SL.TZ0.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the value of A.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}